Classification: Sensitive
From: Privacy
Sent: Monday, 15 September 2025 9:35 am
To: 'Raffaella del Prete' <raffaellanz@icloud.com>
Subject: RE: Privacy Request

Kia ora Raffaella,
Thank you for your email, and please accept our sincere apologies for this =
incident.
We really appreciate you bringing this to our attention so promptly. We tak=
e customer privacy extremely seriously, and we=E2=80=99ve acted quickly to =
contain the matter.
We can confirm that no one other than your email address accessed your fold=
er. Based on our current assessment, it appears that only you could have en=
tered the file in error, and no information has been exposed. To ensure sec=
urity, we=E2=80=99ve deleted both folders and created new ones in ShareFile=
 with secure links. We=E2=80=99ve also notified the Office of the Privacy C=
ommissioner and initiated an investigation to understand the root cause.
Additionally, we=E2=80=99ve asked the team to review your request thoroughl=
y to ensure nothing has been missed and to provide clarity around the redac=
tion of information. We will get back to you within 5 workdays.
Please use the new link below to access your folder. You=E2=80=99ll need to=
 enter your email address, first name, and surname. You can leave the =E2=
=80=9CCompany=E2=80=9D field blank.
https://towernz.sharefile.com/d-s9e40baa94ab04100a6fbeeb731e237e7

Please let me know if you have any problems accessing your folder.

Warm regards
[cid:image001.png@01DC28B0.F9F57340]
Johann Engelbrecht
Compliance and Privacy Advisor
Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142
